  "prompt": "I am graduating in may 2018, should I apply for CDS 1 of 2017?",
  "response": "If you're graduating in May 2018, it would be more suitable to apply for CDS (Combined Defence Services) exam conducted later in 2017 or in early 2018 since you need to be close to completing your degree at the time of applying. CDS exams are typically conducted twice a year, and you should keep an eye on the notifications for CDS (I) and CDS (II) and check the eligibility criteria, including age and educational requirements, to ensure you can apply. \n\nFor CDS I of 2017, you might not yet meet the requirement of having completed your degree, but you should be eligible for CDS II of 2017 or CDS I of 2018. Always refer to the official UPSC notifications for the most accurate information regarding the exams.",
